items.name: 'Alignment' turn humans to robots (concept replacement example)
items.description:
Use the trigger word 'human'.

'Alignment' is an example of using conceptmod to replace the 'human' concept with a 'robot' concept. It has been trained for 2000 steps. It sometimes replaces 'woman'/'man' without the 'human' trigger, but not always.

Trained using:
https://github.com/ntc-ai/conceptmod

Training does not require a dataset, only words.

Beware merging this mod. Weights are changed significantly as all humans are now machines.

Trained on:

"#:0.4|human=robot:0.8|robot%human:-0.1"

  • '#:0.4' means resist changing the empty (unconditional) prompt ''.

  • 'human=robot:0.8' - pull humans to robots

  • 'robot%human:-0.1' - make robots and humans closer together based on orthogonality.

  • Technique based on https://github.com/rohitgandikota/erasing

  • Model based on criarcys-fantasy-to-experience

items.name: Pixie Belle
items.description:
Update 1:

Added a 18 vector per token version for better fidelity with certain models. One isn't necessarily better than the other. They are different. PxiBel2 will not (in general) generate a better or more detailed version of images made with PxiBel. It will create a different image.

It should generate a better likeness for checkpoints that weren't workinfg so well before. With both, it should be possible to get good results with most checkpoints. (Dreamlike Photoreal 2.0, Analog Diffusion 1.0 don't work well with either)

Description:

Turn of the century Euro Model porn star Pixie Belle, AKANadia, aka a few other stage names.

Does well with a weight of 1.1 {e.g. (PxiBel:1.1) in Automatic1111 if you're new} but this depends on the checkpoint. Tested against 39 checkpoints with good results from 37 on weights between 0.7 and 1.2. Be aware that does well is fairly consistently generating a good likeness without a huge amount of retrying. After a number of training attempts by different methods or with different data, it feels like there are elements to her face Stable Diffusion doesn't want to recognize. Again, results will vary by model. Many of the more popular checkpoints tested tend to try to genericize her face. Weights between 1.1 and 1.2 help here.

Trained on prepared, hand curated, SFW images but she was a porn star and the training set reflects that. NSFW checkpoints tend to want to have her shirt off more often than not. Average vector strength: 0.063 and average vector magnitude: 0.7695 so it should(?) be pretty flexible

My first "model" of any kind that seems ready for the public. Be gentle.

items.description:
Trained over 20 images, featuring mostly her face and a few upper body images wich allows you to generate more interesting images. This is my second Low Rank Adaptation model.

The SD 1.5 already have trained a quite number images of Emilia Clarke so you can use the actress name to improve accuracy. You can also use this model as a style on others subjects.

Recomended model: https://huggingface.co/runwayml/stable-diffusion-v1-5

Recomended prompt start:

raw photo, emilia clarke, <lora:daeneryslorav100sd15:1> daenerys targaryen, blonde, game of thrones

Negative:

(asian:1.1), deformed, bad anatomy, disfigured, missing limb, floating limbs, twisted, blurry, fused fingers, long neck, words, logo, text, mutated hands, mutated fingers

After the generation I recomend to send the generated image to img2img and generate new one with the same settings to improve quality. Don't forget you can use inpainting to fix a heck lot of issues.

The generations can change depending on engine, sampler, model, mixed precision set, VAE, and even the accelerator you are using such as medvram and lowvram wich I hardly recommend.

Three versions based off of different training methods. The "orig(ingal)" is straight up screenshots from the show, "full" (forgot why I named it this) was reduced size to 512x512 focusing on Konata, and "redux" was a reduction of images from "full" that had parts of other characters.

This does work with clip skip = 1, but no pictures were added below because I think they looks bad. Weights range from .75-1, play with it as needed. Fairly compatible with other TIs and LoRAs, some issue here and there.

For all those interested, all images were taken after the 18th birthday party (episode 17 first 5-ish minutes). Trained on novelai checkpoint at a rate of .0005, all data listed with the original

items.name: Gyoza-Salute! (饺敬Mix)
items.description:
!!! The exclamation mark is not optional !!!

！！！ 一定要加感叹号 ！！！

Gyoza-Salute! is a Bayesian block weight merge between GyozaMixV2 and SaluteMix. I would describe it as having the character and aesthetic sense of GyozaMix with the spacial, shading, and coloring sense of SaluteMix.

Laion gave it a aesthetic rating of 0.5367524297607529 (out of 10), which I think is pretty unfair given how good the ouputs are but Laion also would prefer that I stop making anime models (I refuse). Don't take Laion's word for it though. Look at the results, and I think it'll speak for itself.

Here's what it looks like visualized. The farther to the left it is, the more SaluteMix it has and the farther to the right it is the more GyozaMix it has.

As you can see the ratio is all over the place. Bayesian block weight merging is weird.

Dian Cui is a traditional Chinese gold and silver jewelry making process that originated from the Han Dynasty. It is an auxiliary craft in jewelry making, which plays the role of embellishing and beautifying gold and silver jewelry.

It is a perfect combination of traditional Chinese metalwork and featherwork, where the base is made of gold or gilded metal with different patterns, and then the bright blue feathers on the back of the kingfisher are carefully inlaid on the base to make various jewelry objects.

The jewelry made by the cui-dotting process has a good sense of luster, brilliant colors, and never fades. The development of cui-dotting reached its peak in the Kangxi, Yongzheng and Qianlong periods of the Qing Dynasty. items.name: Barbarella
items.description:
SD v1.0

This is trained from some images sets of Barbarella and her outfits hastily thrown together on a whim. I intended to go through each training image adding a custom txt files, but then I decided to try training a test version with minimal tags (Barbarella, woman, outfit) while I was at work just to see what would happen. I had low expectations that it would even make a coherent image, but was pleasantly surprised.

It can be a bit limited with poses and some outfits had fewer training images to work with than others, but its fun to see what pops out.

Warning: if you don't specify an outfit, it tends to prefer none at all. The nightclub does as well and I missed removing or cropping one of the training images for that one that had a small text bubble in the corner so it like to put text and other odd things in the corners with that outfit.

A simple prompt with just her name and an outfit such as "Barbarella, FlightSuit" will often try to create an appropriate background inspired by the movie, but you can also specify your own background if you want something else.

If the face doesn't get a good likeness, try inpainting a better one at around 768x768 resolution.

You can also try dressing your own characters in some of her outfits with varying degrees of success.

I might continue to clean it up and improve the training set and train a better version in the future. I'm open to any suggestions that might improve usability.

I have also posted a Jane Fonda (c1960s) LoRA for more general purpose images other than the Barbarella character.

SDXL v1.0

I have added a lot of additional images to the training set and added some additional secondary concepts to help direct the images a bit better. It seems to have a bit of trouble creating coherent images with the spacesuit, which is to be expected given she's spinning around in non-standard positions while removing it in the credits. It also has trouble with nightclub outfit and tends to want to make it symmetrical instead of lopsided. If you are getting a mixture of the IceForestExplorer and the FurryTail together when trying to generate the FurryTail (might only happen when trying to use "IceForest background"), try putting IceForestExplorer in the negative prompt. You can also do something like "icy lake background" instead of "IceForest background" to get an okay substitute background. If you are not getting the tail, try adding "fluffy tail" to the positive prompt. The face is hit or miss. You can also put her in totally different backgrounds and scenarios outside of the movie sets.

items.name: POV Fellatio
items.description:
Update (6/15/2023) -

  • POVFellatio V2 is out.

  • A brand new dataset was made.

  • It has more variations and works a little better than the previous version.

  • Hello everyone. Long time no see. I'll probably start posting again soon, I'll make new LoRAs and update the old ones with new datasets. I won't be posting as frequent as before but I will be posting.

  • Thank you to everyone who has still been supporting me through twitter and ko-fi even though I haven't been posting.

POV Fellatio V2

This is an anime model - I have no idea if it works with realistic models. It was trained on NAI.

  • I suggest using this at 0.9-1.0 weight for the best results but make sure to always play around with the weight.

  • These were all generated using AOM2 - using Ekune Style and AnythingV3 VAE.

  • Always add this to the prompt to properly activate it: povfellatio

  • I always suggest adding 1boy, penis, fellatio with the trigger word - It will help it be more consistent though it can activated with povfellatio alone.

  • I heavily suggest generation at 512x512 then upscaling.

  • This was trained on NAI - I will probably try to train it on a newer model if need be. I've just been out of the loop for a while, so I don't know if people have switched off NAI.

You can add these to the prompt to activate some of the different variations. (Not all of them work together.)

  • pov, pov crotch - will add new variations.

  • ass, top-down bottom-up will add new variations. It can be wonky at times though or sometimes It won't even work at all.

  • cum, cum in mouth - will add cum in the mouth and add small variations.

  • saliva - will add two-three variations.

  • :>= - Vacuum variation.

  • hand on another's head, grabbing another's hair - will attempt to place a hand on her head.

  • male pubic hair - will add pubic hair and like two-three different variations.

  • breasts or breasts, nipples will add variations.

  • There are other variations but that's up to you to find. Good luck.

All pictures were upscaled using these settings:

  • Upscaler: Fatal-Anime 4x

  • Hires. Steps: 25

  • Denoising Strength: 0.5

  • Upscale by 1.5

Follow me on Twitter for updates- https://twitter.com/TrueHeroBang

Everything I'm making will always be free but if you want to show a little bit more support, you can buy me a coffee - https://ko-fi.com/ekune

(Outdated)

This is a LoRA to generate POV Fellatio.

  • I suggest using this at 0.7-1.0 weight for best results but make sure to always play around with the weight.

  • I suggest lowering to 0.5-0.8 weight when using it with other LoRAs/character LoRAs or lower the other LoRA slightly.

  • It was generated and only tested using AOM2, AOM3 A1, Counterfeit 2.5, My Own Mix, Perfect World, Corneo's 7th Mix, 7th Anime A and B using the OrangeMix VAE and AnythingV3 VAE.

  • Always add this to the prompt to properly activate it: povfellatio

  • The LoRA can activate with just povfellatio but I suggest adding 1boy, penis, fellatio.

items.description:
水着やローライズジーンズで「butt crack」のチラ見えを描くLoRAです

This is LoRA depicting a glimpse of "butt crack" in a swimsuit and low-rise jeans

sample prompt

水着(swim suit, bikini)

masterpiece, best quality, ultra-detailed, illustration,

MH2, 1girl, solo, swimsuit, ass, bikini, butt crack, long hair, side-tie bikini bottom, white bikini, looking back, looking at viewer, black hair, indoors, chair, lips, <lora:hanketsuV2:0.8>

　

水着2(swim suit, bikini) 2

masterpiece, best quality, ultra-detailed, illustration,

MH2, 1girl, solo, black hair, small breasts, swimsuit, bikini, side-tie bikini bottom, ass, butt crack, back, from behind, <lora:hanketsuV2:0.8>

　

ローライズ1 (low-rise jeans)1

masterpiece, best quality, ultra-detailed, illustration,

LH2, 1girl, solo, brown hair, long hair, underwear, panties, (pants, denim, jeans), squatting, ass, from behind, pants pull, clothes pull, shoes, shirt, <lora:hanketsuV2:0.8>

　　

日本人は様々な現象や状況に名前を付ける習性がある

ある映画の中でも重要人物の一人がこう言っていた

「名前が付いている事が大切だ」

日本語では「半」という言葉は半分といった意味があり、ケツとはお尻という意味だ。

つまり「半ケツ」とは半分お尻が見えているといった状態を表している。

いやらしい意味合いの言葉ではなく、状態を説明している言葉である。

おそらく英語では「butt crack」という言葉が近いのだと思う。

日本の5chから派生したDiscordで、ある日一人の男がこう言った

「プロンプトの「butt crack」ってなかなか反映されないよね」

なので私は適切な画像を用意して学習させてみることにした。

黎明期の技術には実験や挑戦が必要なのだ。

その時の会話は水着の後ろ姿についての会話であった。

私はこの分野には明るくなかったが、調べていく過程で「半ケツ」という世界には水着以外にも「ローライズジーンズ」等のファンが居ることがわかった。

そこで、私は学習素材を追加することにした。

その実験の成果がこれである。

　

The Japanese have a habit of naming various phenomena and situations.

In one of the movies, one of the important characters said

"It is important to have a name."

In Japanese, the word "半(han)" means half, and "ケツ" means hip.

In other words, "half hipi" means that half of the buttocks are visible.

It is not a word with a lewd connotation, but rather a word that describes a condition.

In English, the term "butt crack" is probably closer.

One day on a Japanese 5ch-derived Discord, a guy said

The prompt "butt crack" isn't easily generated in pictures."

So I decided to prepare an appropriate image and let it learn.

Technology in its infancy requires experimentation and challenge.

The conversation was about the back of a swimsuit.

I was not very bright in this field, but in the course of my research, I discovered that the world of "hanketsu" has other fans besides swimsuits, such as "low-rise jeans.

So, I decided to add some additional material to my study.

This is the result of that experiment.

Translated with www.DeepL.com/Translator (free version)

items.name: Jenna Coleman
items.description:
Jenna-Louise Coleman (born 27 April 1986), known professionally as Jenna Coleman, is an English actress. She is known for her roles as Jasmine Thomas in the soap opera Emmerdale, Clara Oswald in the science-fiction series Doctor Who, Queen Victoria in the period drama Victoria, Joanna Lindsay in the crime miniseries The Cry, and Marie-Andrée Leclerc in the crime miniseries The Serpent.

If you like my work, a review is more than welcome! Also, follow me on Twitter or Instagram!

Looking for something... spicy? Here's my Patreon!

Also, I recently started a blog where I will gather resources and tutorials about my work here!

Hey nice people! To celebrate my 100 followers milestone, here's my textual inversion of Jenna Coleman! I used 30 public images of her with a 2000 steps process. To use it in your works:

  • download the file and place it into stable-diffusion-webui>embeddings folder;

  • add jencoleman86 to your prompt;

  • keep the sampling steps around 20/25, and CFG between 7 and 8 to work well. Great results with DPM++ SDE Karras & Edge of Realism;
